<h1><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-check"></i>Project and Program Management - Initiation</h1>
<p>
<%= link_to image_tag("basediscover4atext.png",:size => '150x70', alt: "Project Mgt"  ), page_path('projmgt'),class: 'pull-left' %>        	
		<p> Project initiation is  where you develop key documents and processes. This can also be call the <strong>discovery</strong> phase to link it to
			our common  <%= link_to ' IT management structure', page_path('bizopsprocess')  %>. This activity is a continuation of the orgainisations strategic planning process,
			where oragnisational goals are defined. We should acknowledge here that the organisation has already done a lot of work prior to starting this project
			and we are just moving to the next phase in the continuing change driven by organisations. We should already be able to see strategic business plans, prioritisation of the plans
			and goals and a good description of what the organisation wants to achieve with this project. </p>
			<p>
			In this phase, you produce a Project Management Plan which contains information like a high level scope, project charter, how the project will run. 
			what the company wants to achieve and how this is measured. Essentially what success looks like, aligned to the strategic plan. 
			You produce a high level estimate of cost, resources and duration as well as a strawman plan, team structure, a communication plan
			(including all stakeholders), a high level risk assessment and quality plan. You may also need to consider 3rd party vendors in your plan.
			</p>  
        							 		
		<hr />
		<hr />
		<hr />
